cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.AI, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper focuses on detecting stealth software and cyber-attacks which use malware, which falls under the domain of cyber security. 
2. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper presents new detection methods and an architecture of a software tool, which involves software engineering principles. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the use of CUDA enabled GPU hardware to speed up memory forensics, which falls under the domain of parallel computing. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper mentions the use of digital photogrammetry and the Zipf Mandelbrot law, which are techniques used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper mentions disassembling memory content and analyzing the output, which involves programming languages and low-level system programming.
